        {
            "id": "b7a56a9d86964c67af314",
            "questionText": "An alpha particle (charge $!$q = +3.2 \\times 10^{-19} C$!$, mass $!$m = 6.64 \\times 10^{-27} kg$!$) is moving with a velocity of $!$v = 5 \\times 10^5 m/s$!$ in a region with a uniform electric field of $!$E = 1000 N/C$!$ pointing upwards and a uniform magnetic field of magnitude $!$B$!$ (which has been previously set so that the particle passes through the region undeflected). If the electric field is now turned off, determine the radius $!$R$!$ of the circular path that the alpha particle follows due to the magnetic field alone.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "68eb88c56863494683108",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by considering that the particle passes through the crossed fields undeflected. This implies that the magnetic and electric forces balance. Identify the formula that relates the particle's speed $!$v$!$, the electric field $!$E$!$, and the magnetic field $!$B$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "869566af-fb78-4d6f-b591-4f86eae31f82"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\frac{E}{B}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$B = \\frac{qE}{mv}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$F = qE$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "6f31ebe5a18748609c6e8",
                    "stepText": "Now that you have selected the correct relation, use it to calculate the magnetic field strength $!$B$!$. Use the relationship $!$B = \\frac{E}{v}$!$ by substituting the given values for $!$E$!$ and $!$v$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.002"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "T",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "869566af-fb78-4d6f-b591-4f86eae31f82"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "618d62397f0f475aa868c",
                    "stepText": "Next, once the electric field is turned off, the magnetic force acts as the centripetal force, making the particle follow a circular path. Identify the formula that equates the magnetic force to the centripetal force.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "f34446c8-9452-48c0-ab50-0cb3fd1b9679"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$qvB = m\\frac{v^2}{R}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$qvB = \\frac{mv}{R}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$qE = m\\frac{v^2}{R}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "42d65402683b46128c571",
                    "stepText": "Finally, rearrange the chosen equation to solve for the radius $!$R$!$. Substitute the numerical values for the mass $!$m$!$, speed $!$v$!$, charge $!$q$!$, and the magnetic field $!$B$!$ to calculate $!$R$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
